To read TRUST results files with OpenDX:
-----------------------------------------

Run OpenDx with the command:
$DXROOT/dx (or DX under TRUST environment).

Click on Run Visual Programs to run a .net Program
located under $TRUST_ROOT/Outils/lata2dx

For example, choose simple_importer.net for a single domain
or geometry_multidomains.net for several domains.

On the Panel, import your .lata results file. Choose
the element type and select binary if you post-process
with binary format.

Click Show color field and Show glyph to update
the two lists containing positions, time, scalar
and vectorial fields.

UPDATE March, 8th 2005
----------------------

We switched to a new version of the lata-to-dx converter
which is lata2dx.
Old .net programs are still here for reference but they don't work since
they use the old filter.

The new reference .net file is "post_lata_generique"


Mise a jour 6 mars 2006
-----------------------
Correction d'un bug avec "regularize" sur les gros maillages,
Postraitement des vitesses aux faces en VDF avec OpenDx

Pour visualiser les vitesses aux faces:
- ecrire le champ aux faces au format lata (comme en vef).

- ajouter les options "regularize=1e-6 dualmesh" dans la GUI du post_lata_generique.

- pour visualiser la composante x du champ de vitesse, faire un plan de coupe (en 3d) et
  mettre "v.x" dans "Compute expression". On voit alors un champ constant sur chaque
  volume de controle des faces de vitesse x. Idem pour y et z.

- en 2d il faut utiliser Simple shade a la place de cut plane (non teste)
